==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catastrophism
<hw>Ca*tas"tro*phism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>The doctrine that the geological changes in the earth's crust have
been caused by the sudden action of violent physical causes; -- opposed
to the doctrine of <contr>uniformism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catastrophist</ent>⟦br⟧
